\fs26 \'97 INFO ABOUT THE PROGRAM AND AND ERRORS/BUGS \'97\
The tower of Hanoi program calculates the moves required to move a number of disks from a tower to another without ever putting a bigger disk on a smaller one. The towers command can be used to run the program with 0, 1 or 3 parameters in the format ./\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 towers numberDisks fromTower destTower\
\
The program works as intended with no bugs. \
\
For an invalid input, it does not explicitly state why the input is wrong and just gives a general error message. It is done this way because in the lab manual it only requires an error message and going through all the possible error reasons to print a specific message is unnecessary in this case.\
\outl0\strokewidth0 \
