\cf0 \'97 QUESTIONS\'97\
1. The recursion will be invoked as: \
towers(5, 2, 3)\
..towers(4, 2, 1)\
....towers(3, 2, 3)\
......towers(2, 2, 1)\
........towers(1, 2, 3)\
..........towers(0, 2, 1)\
So recursion 1 will be towers(4, 2, 1)\
\
2. 5 recursive calls will be made. \
\
3. The move is Move #1: From Tower 2 to Tower 3 so the stdout will be: 2 3\
\
\cb3 4.\cf4 \cb5  \cf4 \cb5 \outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec6 the second recursive call is invoked as \cf0 \cb3 \strokec2 towers(3, 2, 3)\cf7 \strokec7 .\cf0 \cb1 \outl0\strokewidth0 \
\
\
1. Towers(8, 1, 2) will print 255 lines to stdout. This number was achieved by moving the output to a file towers812 then counting the lines with the unix command \'93wc -l towers812\'94. It is the same result when mathematical formula for number of moves (2^n)-1 is used, (2^8)-1 = 255.\
